  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation de libffi</title>
    <para>Installez <application>libffi</application> en lançant les
    commandes suivantes&nbsp;:</para>
<screen>
<userinput>sed -e '/^includesdir/ s:$(libdir)/@PACKAGE_NAME@-@PACKAGE_VERSION@/include:$(includedir):' \
    -i include/Makefile.in &amp;&amp;
sed -e '/^includedir/ s:${libdir}/@PACKAGE_NAME@-@PACKAGE_VERSION@/include:@includedir@:' \
    -e 's/^Cflags: -I${includedir}/Cflags:/' \
    -i libffi.pc.in        &amp;&amp;
./configure --prefix=/usr --disable-static &amp;&amp;
make</userinput>
</screen>
    <para>
      Pour tester les résultats, tapez: <command>make check</command>.
    </para>
    <para>Maintenant, en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem>&nbsp;:</para>
<screen role="root">
<userinput>make install</userinput>
</screen>
  </sect2>
  <sect2 role="commands">
    <title>Explications des commandes</title>
    <para><command>sed ... include/Makefile.in</command> et
    <command>sed ... libffi.pc.in</command>: Fait que le paquet installe les entêtes dans
    /usr/include au lieu de /usr/lib/libffi-&libffi-version;/include.</para>
    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
      href="../../xincludes/static-libraries.xml"/>
  </sect2>
